cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the complexity of learning and approximation of functions, which suggests that it could belong to categories related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of concentration of measure inequalities and the focus on submodular and XOS functions also suggest categories related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the study of self-bounding functions could also fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
